#ROOMS
#5550
The Withered Gate~
A wind colder than winter drifts across this quarter of the pasture, carrying the smell of wet ash, old incense, and turned graves. The mud is churned by cart wheels, boots, and hoofprints that end abruptly at the edge of shallow ditches lined with corpse-lilies. At The Withered Gate, the earth has been salted, blessed, and cursed so many times that nothing grows true; even moss climbs in funereal spirals.~
