#5604
The Bonewind Gap~
Pale moths orbit guttering lanterns tied to iron crooks, and their wings leave powdery crescents on the blackened stalks. Scarecrows with ossuary masks tilt toward the lane, their straw ribs packed with raven feathers, wax drippings, and saintly bone chips. In The Bonewind Gap, the darkness feels cultivated rather than natural, as if an unseen caretaker waters shadow the way farmers once watered wheat.~
